                        Sentinel</b>
                        </font><font face="arial" size="1"> - Thursday, May 11, 2000 at 9:53 AM</font><font face="arial" size="2"><br>
						
						
						hybrid exp penalties unfair? and the first class to make level 60 was a ranger? :)<p>it's not THAT bad.. they do get all those handy spells. As a warrior I would love to have healing, snare, damage shields, invisibility, sow and that's just rangers.<br>SK's get invisibility and feign death and some lifetaps.. even a pet that acts as a constant dot(not secondary tank).<br>I've seen paladins use LoH to shift the tide of a particularly hard fight many times.. AND they have greater heal for downtime to save the healers a bit of mana..not to mention root.<br>All that for just a little exp penalty? hybrids should quit complaining.
						
						</font>
					  </td>
                    </tr>
					 
					
				    <tr>
                      <td width="6%" valign="top" align="center" bgcolor="bfbf80" background=""><font face="arial" color="4a0000" size="3"><b>2.</b></font></td>
                      <td width="94%" valign="top" bgcolor="CDCD9C"><font face="arial" size="2"><b>Response from:
                        CrazyMofo</b>
                        </font><font face="arial" size="1"> - Thursday, May 11, 2000 at 1:03 PM</font><font face="arial" size="2"><br>
						
						
						I currently play 2 hybrids. They are very worth it in the end. The experience penalty is a drag. A real drag for ShadowKnights, like my Iksar. Iksars will get penalized for the following:<br>#1. Evil race<br>#2. Evil class<br>#3. Evil deity<br>#4. Hybrid<p>all of those things make shadowknights have a rough time. Harm Touch is all and good, but it's ridiculous. A wizard can cast 1 spell and outdamage my hard touch. The spells are weak. Pets are nice, but when the level spread grows larger, your pet barely hits the monster at all. I don't want to complain too much, but rangers are shafted heavily. Yes, they have dual wield, but what else can they boast about? a level 39 sow? a level 49 wolf form? Druids get track, so that's not unique. They get shafted in the respect that they get skill capped really early. Dual Wield at like 130 i believe, and double attack a bit later. In a PvP fight, I dueled a warrior 2 levels beneath me, and it was rough. I won in the end, but it was real close. <p>Rangers need some help I think. And giving the paladins and shadowknights critical hits would be nice too. Anyone else with the same view?
						
						</font>
					  </td>
                    </tr>
					 
					
