						yes, I'm the one who made the original news post. First off, I want to thank the EQ realms staff for posting my news. I found that pretty neat. secondly, I think I should appologize to Dr. Evil because he is right in many aspects.<p>1) Iksar do have faction limitations more harsh than the "good" aligned races. Yes, there is a faction cap.<br>2) Iksar monks have a harder time gaining experience than human monks.<br>3) Humans are average at best. Their stats are all around 75, and they lack some flavor other races have.<p>To get on with my reply, I simply wanted other's opinions about weather or not players would abandon their human monks and go with the Iksar monks from a purely statistical standpoint. Again, I do apologize for misquoting some facts about the new iksar race. I quoted some STATISTICAL issues about the iksar (BytorX1, I realize the importance of role playing and that's not what this thread is about. I am not understanding why some of you choose to flame this question?).<p>But Hey! Some of you guys had some great responses that I really liked to hear.<p>a) drakkis, thanks for the gordon post<br>b) dantes, interesting thoughts on NOBODY wanting to be human<br>c) faldrick, I didn't know the tail whip replaced dragon punch<br>d) amaprotu, thanks for realizing I was trying to compare both races of monks at that level, not how hard it was to get there.<br>e) kurgan, pretty funny stuff. Verant sure is confusing<br>f) veranon, ozzman, zenon, and orionmbeadling, good comments<p>Anyways, I guess I have some more issues to raise. I made a quote about how unreal I thought it was to say that Iksar monks wouldn't be as good as human monks in the later levels. The faction STILL is not all that important because at 60, it's rather unimportant to have a measly guard chasing you down with his toothpick sword. And it's true that an Iksar won't get as much experience in his Bub-O-Meter as a Human when slaying NPC's, but I fail to see how it's harder for an iksar to gain levels? With regeneration, it would be very easy to hunt 'till you're encumbered. <p>So does anyone else think that, on a purely "statistical" standpoint, that poeople would choose to hang their human monks up on the self to collect dust behind that new shiny Iksar Monk?<br>
						
						</font>
