						A long long time ago I advocated about the unfairness of many of the exp penalties.  They use the same arguments today, but now they also use the "its been in production for a year" one too.  If they had let the beta run a little longer, they might have gotten some more feedback in time to have changed some things.  Many beta testers felt it ended a little to soon.  There is nothing we can do now though, but at least they have the knowledge for EQ 2 or what have you.
						
